cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a novel approach for anomaly detection using a multi-hypotheses autoencoder. This involves learning the data distribution of the foreground more efficiently, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach also involves using a discriminator to prevent artificial data modes not supported by data, which is a common technique in adversarial learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents results on a real anomaly detection task, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR).
